    <text>
        <body>
            <div type="edition" xml:space="preserve"><head>Text</head><ab><lb n="1"/>
                Dis Manibus <lb n="2"/>Cocceius Vitales <note>sic</note> vixsit <note>sic</note> <lb n="3"/>annis L et <expan><abbr>Coc</abbr><ex>ceia</ex></expan> Iulia co<lb break="no" n="4"/>niunxs <note>sic</note> eius vixsit <note>sic</note> annis <lb n="5"/>XL obiti ad villam suam Coc<lb break="no" n="6"/>ceius Clemens et <expan><abbr>Coc</abbr><ex>ceius</ex></expan> He<lb break="no" n="7"/>lius <expan><abbr>fili</abbr><ex>i</ex></expan> patri et matri <supplied reason="lost">be</supplied><lb break="no" n="8"/>ne merentibus titulum <lb n="9"/>posuerunt
            </ab></div>
            <div type="commentary">
                <p>3 aneinanderpassende Fragmente erhalten. Oberhalb des Inschriftfeldes ein nach rechts sprengender Reiterf; darüber Totenmahlrelief. Häufig hederae als Worttrenner. (B): CIL III: Z. 7/8: be/ne.</p>
            </div>
